1 isn't true. o1 doesn't have access to a Python interpreter unless you explicitly grant it access.If you call the OpenAI API for o1 and ask it to multiply two large numbers it cannot use Python to help it.Try this:    curl https://api.openai.com/v1/responses \
      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
      -H "Authorization: Bearer $OPENAI_API_KEY" \
      -d '{
        "model": "o1",
        "input": "Multiply 87654321 × 98765432",
        "reasoning": {
          "effort": "medium",
          "summary": "detailed"
        }
      }'

Here's what I got back just now: https://gist.github.com/simonw/a6438aabdca7eed3eec52ed7df64e...o1 correctly answered the multiplication by running a long multiplication process entirely through reasoning tokens.
